=== M === {| class="wikitable" !Dacian name !Possible etymology !Attestation !Notes |- |Moskon | |Inscription on silver coins about a 3rd century BC getic king | |- |Mucapor | |Inscription at [[Alba Iulia|Apulum]]{{sfn|Piso|2001|p=425}} that reads: ''Mucatra, son of Brasus, had a son and heir Mucapor Mucatralis''{{sfn|Kugener|Herrman|1977|p=516}} |These names are Thracians and Dacians (as Mucapor is attested as Dacian and as Thracian name).{{sfn|Mommsen|1887|p=225}} The names containing Muca are found in Thracian but also in the proper Geto-Dacian names{{sfn|Dumistracel|1988|p=395}} |- |Mucatra | |Inscription at [[Alba Iulia|Apulum]]{{sfn|Piso|2001|p=425}} that reads: ''Mucatra, son of Brasus, had a son and heir Mucapor Mucatralis''{{sfn|Kugener|Herrman|1977|p=516}} |These names are probably Thracian, not Dacian, as Mucapor is attested as an ethnic Thracian name (see refs above).{{Citation needed|date=July 2011}} |}
