=== P === {| class="wikitable" !Dacian name !Possible etymology !Attestation !Notes |- |[[Petoporus]], Petipor | |Name of a Dacian prince {{sfn|Tomaschek|1883|p=407}} | |- |Pieporus |The first element Pie is analogue by initial and vocalism with the name Pie-figoi of a Dacian tribe mentioned by Ptolemy.{{sfn|Tomaschek|1883|p=407}} The second element Porus is often met with Dacian and also with Bithynian (a Thracian tribe) names. It can be explain by the root *par ‘replenish’ nourish or *pa-la ‘king’{{sfn|Tomaschek|1883|p=407}} |Name of a king of the [[Costoboci]] (inscription C.1 Rom. VI, No. 1801).{{sfn|Tomaschek|1883|p=407}}{{sfn|Dana|2006|p=117}} |NOTE: some scholars consider this a Thracian name.{{Citation needed|date=July 2011}} |- |Pouridour | |Ostracon of Dacian cavalry recruited after the Roman conquest and stationed in East Egypt {{sfn|Dana|2003|p=176}} | |}
